    <div class="py-5 dog-walk-banner">
      <h2 style="color: #032B22; font-family: 'Abril Fatface', serif !important">Why Dog Walking is Important</h2>
      <p class="font-dog-walk-guide">Dog walking isn’t just about getting your pup out of the house—it’s crucial for their physical health, mental stimulation, and socialisation. Here’s why:</p>
      <ul class="font-dog-walk-guide">
        <li><strong>Exercise:</strong> Regular walks help maintain a healthy weight and build muscle.</li>
        <li><strong>Mental Stimulation:</strong> New environments and experiences keep your dog's mind sharp.</li>
        <li><strong>Behavior:</strong> Consistent walks help curb unwanted behaviors like excessive barking or chewing.</li>
        <li><strong>Bonding:</strong> Walking together strengthens the relationship between you and your dog.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="py-5">
      <h2 style="color: #032B22; font-family: 'Abril Fatface', serif !important">Our Dog Walking Services</h2>
      <p class="font-dog-walk-guide">At Walks & Wags Co., we offer two types of walks designed to suit every dog's needs:</p>
      <div class="row mt-3 services-dog-guide">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3 style="color: #032B22; font-family: 'Abril Fatface', serif !important;">Solo Dog Walks</h3>
          <p class="font-dog-walk-guide">One-on-one adventures with your pup in nature—whether it's a peaceful stroll in the woods or a fun hike in the fields. Our solo walks are tailored to provide gentle exercise and mental stimulation.</p>
          <%= image_tag "solo_walks.png", loading:"lazy", class:"w-100" %>
          <a class="font-dog-walk-guide text-center mt-3 button" href="/services">Learn More About Solo Walks</a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3 style="color: #032B22; font-family: 'Abril Fatface', serif !important;">Group Dog Walks</h3>
          <p class="font-dog-walk-guide">Social walks with 3-4 other friendly dogs! Let your dog make new friends while exploring local parks, fields, and woodlands. It’s a fun and safe way for your pup to socialise and exercise.</p>
          <%= image_tag "group_walks.png", loading:"lazy", class:"w-100" %>
          <a class="font-dog-walk-guide text-center mt-3 button" href="/services">Learn More About Group Walks</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tips for a Great Walk Section -->
    <div class="py-5">
      <h2 style="color: #032B22; font-family: 'Abril Fatface', serif !important;">Tips for a Successful Dog Walk</h2>
      <p class="font-dog-walk-guide">To ensure your dog enjoys the best possible walking experience, here are some useful tips:</p>
      <ul class="font-dog-walk-guide">
        <li><strong>Use the Right Leash:</strong> Choose a leash that is comfortable for both you and your dog.</li>
        <li><strong>Stay Hydrated:</strong> Bring water for your dog, especially on longer walks or hot days.</li>
        <li><strong>Use Positive Reinforcement:</strong> Reward your dog with treats or praise during and after walks.</li>
        <li><strong>Follow the Route:</strong> Stick to familiar routes until your dog is comfortable with new ones.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="font-dog-walk-guide">For more detailed walking tips, check out our <a href="/blogs/best-leashes-for-different-dog-breeds">blog post on the best leashes for different breeds</a>.</p>
    </div>

